# =============================================================
# Rust / Cargo build artefacts (every crate has its own target/)
# =============================================================
**/target/

# =============================================================
# fdev build output — each contract / delegate crate has its own
# `build/freenet/` subdir with the compiled WASM. Regenerated by
# `scripts/dev-publish.sh`.
# =============================================================
# Each contract / delegate crate's per-publish artefact dir
# (`<crate>/build/freenet/<wasm>`); fdev rewrites it on every
# `fdev build`. The committed snapshots that gate prod-publish live
# elsewhere — `published-delegate/identity_delegate.wasm` and
# `published-contract/<name>/<name>_contract.wasm`, both tracked.
**/build/freenet/

# =============================================================
# Trunk dev/release bundle. `trunk serve` + `trunk build` write
# the wasm-bindgen output, copy-file assets, and the rendered
# index.html here. Always regenerable from the Rust source.
# =============================================================
frontend/dist/

# =============================================================
# Runtime artefact — `dev-publish.sh` writes the eight contract
# instance ids / code hashes for the local node into this file.
# Node-specific, regenerated on every (re-)publish.
# =============================================================
frontend/dev-keys.json

# =============================================================
# Build artefacts staged into the frontend bundle — `dev-publish.sh`
# / `prod-publish.sh` copy the freshly-built delegate + presence-
# contract WASM here after `fdev build`. Frontend bundles them via
# trunk's copy-file rule. Regenerated on every (re-)publish.
#
# NOT to be confused with the byte-stability snapshots in
# `published-delegate/` and `published-contract/<name>/` — those
# ARE tracked in git and are the gate `scripts/check-*-byte-equal.sh`
# enforces. See docs/delegate-stability.md.
# =============================================================
frontend/identity_delegate.wasm
frontend/presence_contract.wasm

# =============================================================
# Logs left by `dev-watch.sh` / `trunk serve` / various tests.
# =============================================================
*.log
/tmp/idle-*

# =============================================================
# Editor / OS noise.
# =============================================================
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# Direnv + secrets-by-convention.
.envrc
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Backup files emitted by prod-publish.sh on every patch of keys.rs.
*.rs.bak

# Auto-skip cache. `prod-publish.sh` writes the source-tree hashes
# of identity-delegate / presence-contract after every successful
# publish; the next run reads them to decide which stages can be
# auto-skipped. Pure operator-side state, never committed.
frontend/.prod-publish-state

# Operator-specific website contract id captured by `prod-publish.sh`
# and consumed by `prod-update-webapp.sh` to find the website to
# update. Different operators publishing to different nodes get
# different ids — committing would create a merge-conflict footgun
# without any shared benefit (the runtime URL already exposes the
# id via `webapp_contract_id()`).
frontend/prod-webapp-id.txt

# Snapshot directories: we commit *only* `sha256.txt` + `code_hash.txt`
# + the README. The raw WASM (and the fdev-wrapped form) are not
# committed — they're hundreds of KB of stored bandwidth per release.
# The byte-equality gate verifies drift via `sha256sum` against the
# committed hash; reproducing the exact bytes comes from re-running
# the locked build against the committed sources (Cargo.lock +
# rust-toolchain.toml + `=x.y.z` pins make rebuilds deterministic).
# See docs/delegate-stability.md.
published-delegate/*.wasm
published-delegate/*.fdev
published-contract/*/*.wasm
published-contract/*/*.fdev
